title: About
text:
I’m a dad, husband, runner, handyman and engineer.
I’ve been a software engineer for over 12 years. My career started in semiconductor manufacturing where I developed and maintained manufacturing automation systems. Eventually I found my way into software consulting.
I’ve worked on several .NET projects in a variety of industries and varying solution type. Some projects highlights include building and improving web applications, developing identity solutions, event-based systems, modernizing systems, and data engineering.
Away from my keyboard, you’ll usually find me running, hanging out with my family, fixing things around the house, and building things.

title: Welcome
text:
What you can expect
I intend this blog to be mostly a technical blog on my journey through the rest of my career. You can expect to see articles about topics in Machine Learning, .NET, C#, python and other technical topics.
I’m not limiting the posts strictly technical topics. I have many other roles in my life besides being a software engineer and consultant. I’m a father of three, I’m a husband, I run, I build things, I fix things, I break things, I like cars the list goes on. You might see these things sprinkled in.
